item.description:
Cloud computing is gaining popularity as a cost-effective alternative to traditional data centers. However, a new competitor called &ldquo;clod&rdquo; computing is emerging, boasting even lower costs.
](http://www.sysnito.com/?crid=11591&linkID=145&refid=Telexplainer-Clod)Clod computing minimizes infrastructure expenses by utilizing readily available, discarded computers. Chip-On-A-Shingle, a clod computing startup, defines a &ldquo;clod&rdquo; as a network of interconnected old computers and devices that collectively provide impressive processing power.
This approach is viable due to the abundance of still functional computers being discarded simply because they are outdated.
